# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok supporters of thailand 's ousted prime minister thaksin shinawatra vowed on saturday to stage another major rally against the council for national security -lrb- cns -rrb- , one day after thaksin addressed thousands of them via a recorded tape .
# ::alignments
(v / vow-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (s / supply-01)
            :ARG1-of (o / oust-01
                  :ARG0 (p2 / person
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Thaksin"
                              :op2 "Shinawatra")
                        :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG1 (c / country
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Thailand"))
                              :ARG2 (m / minister
                                    :mod (p3 / prime))))))
      :ARG1 (s2 / stage-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (r / rally-01
                  :ARG1 (c2 / council
                        :topic (s3 / security
                              :mod (n3 / nation)))
                  :ARG2 (o2 / oppose-01
                        :ARG1 c2)
                  :mod (a / another)
                  :ARG1-of (m2 / major-02))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (s4 / saturday))
            :time (a2 / after
                  :op1 (a3 / address-03
                        :ARG0 p2
                        :ARG1 (p4 / person
                              :quant (m3 / multiple
                                    :op1 1000))
                        :medium (t / tape
                              :ARG1-of (r2 / record-01)))
                  :quant (t2 / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 1
                        :unit (d2 / day)))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok sears , roebuck &amp; co. said it agreed to acquire orchard supply hardware stores corp. for $ ## a share in cash , or a total of about $ ### million .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (c / company
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Sears"
                  :op2 ","
                  :op3 "&"
                  :op4 "amp"
                  :op5 "Co."))
      :ARG1 (a / agree-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a2 / acquire-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (c2 / company
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Orchard"
                              :op2 "Supply"
                              :op3 "and"
                              :op4 "Capital")
                        :ARG0-of (s2 / supply-01
                              :ARG1 (s3 / store
                                    :mod (h / hardware))))
                  :ARG3 (o / orchard)
                  :ARG4 o
                  :ARG0-of s2
                  :ARG1 (c3 / cash)))
      :ARG1-of (t / total-01
            :ARG2 (a3 / about
                  :op1 (m / monetary-quantity
                        :quant 10000000
                        :unit (d / dollar)))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the americans halt shipments of fuel oil to north korea .
# ::alignments
(h / halt-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :mod (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "America")))
      :ARG1 (s / ship-01
            :ARG1 (o / oil
                  :mod (f / fuel))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "North"
                        :op2 "Korea"))))

# ::id 3 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok hillary rodham clinton and rudolph giuliani are not even declared candidates , yet each has spent millions of dollars on what is shaping up as the costliest u.s. senate race in history .
# ::alignments
(d / declare-01
      :polarity -
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (p / person
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Hillary"
                        :op2 "Rodham"
                        :op3 "Clinton"))
            :op2 (p2 / person
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Rudolph"
                        :op2 "Giuliani")))
      :ARG2 (c / candidate)
      :mod (e / even)
      :concession-of (s / spend-01
            :ARG0 a
            :ARG1 (t / thing
                  :ARG1-of (s2 / shape-up-02
                        :ARG2 (r / race-02
                              :ARG3 (g / government-organization
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Senate")
                                    :location (c2 / country
                                          :name (n4 / name
                                                :op1 "U.S.")))
                              :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                                    :ARG2 (c3 / cost-01
                                          :ARG1 r)
                                    :ARG3 (m / most)
                                    :ARG5 (h2 / history)))))
            :ARG3 (m2 / multiple
                  :op1 (m3 / monetary-quantity
                        :quant 1000000
                        :unit (d2 / dollar)))))

            :weekday (f2 / friday)))

# ::id 5 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok at least eight families whose children died from mad cow disease after treatment with human growth hormones won a high court battle friday for the right to claim compensation from the government .
# ::alignments

      :ARG0 (f / family
            :ARG0-of (h / have-rel-role-91
                  :ARG1 (c / child
                        :ARG1-of (d / die-01
                              :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                                    :ARG0 (d2 / disease
                                          :name (n / name
                                                :op1 "mad"
                                                :op2 "cow"))
                                    :time (a / after
                                          :op1 (t / treat-03
                                                :ARG1 c
                                                :ARG2 (h2 / hormone
                                                      :mod (g / grow-01
                                                            :ARG1 (h3 / human)))))))
                        :ARG2 c))
            :quant (a2 / at-least
                  :op1 8))
      :ARG2 (r / right-05
            :ARG1 f
            :ARG2 (c3 / claim-01
                  :ARG0 f
                  :ARG1 (c4 / compensate-01
                        :ARG0 (g2 / government-organization
                              :ARG0-of (g3 / govern-01))
                        :ARG2 f)))
      :ARG3 (c5 / court
            :ARG1-of (h4 / high-02))
      :time (d3 / date-entity
            :weekday (f2 / friday)))

                        :op1 "Spain")

                        :name (n5 / name

      :domain (d3 / day
            :ARG0-of (s / stun-01)))

# ::alignments

      :ARG0 (g / government-organization

                  :ARG1 (c / country
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "South"
                              :op2 "Korea"))))
      :ARG1 (r / report-01
            :ARG0 (m / media
                  :ARG1-of (l / local-02))
            :ARG1 (a / agree-01
                  :ARG0 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (s / seoul)
                        :op2 (c2 / company
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Washington")))
                  :ARG1 (d2 / delay-01
                        :ARG0 a2
                        :ARG1 (t / transfer-01
                              :ARG0 a2
                              :ARG1 (c3 / control-01
                                    :time (w / wartime)
                                    :ARG1-of (o / operate-01))
                              :ARG2 (c4 / country
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "United"
                                          :op2 "States"))
                              :ARG3 c
                              :direction (b / back))
                        :ARG1-of (s2 / schedule-01
                              :ARG3 (e / event)
                              :mod (o2 / original)))
                  :mod (v / virtual))
            :time (d3 / date-entity
                  :weekday (t2 / thursday))))

# ::alignments
(a / assault-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (a2 / attack-01)
            :ARG1-of (a3 / arm-01
                  :ARG2 (a4 / and
                        :op1 (w / weapon
                              :mod (a5 / automatic))
                        :op2 (g / grenade
                              :ARG1-of (p2 / propel-01
                                    :ARG0 (r / rocket)))
                        :op3 (c / car
                              :mod (s / suicide)
                              :quant (a6 / at-least
                                    :op1 1)))))
      :ARG1 (e / embassy
            :mod (c2 / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "U.S."))
            :location (c3 / city
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 c2
                        :ARG2 (c4 / capital))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (w2 / wednesday)))

                  :ARG1 (d / department

                  :ARG2 (o / official)))

            :ARG0 f
            :ARG0-of (m / move-01
                  :ARG1-of (f2 / fast-02))
            :ARG0-of (r / rip-01
                  :ARG1 (h2 / home
                        :location (c / city-district
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 " queens")
                              :ARG1-of (ii / include-91
                                    :ARG2 (c2 / city-district
                                          :quant 5
                                          :part-of (c3 / city
                                                :name (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 "New"
                                                      :op2 "York"))))))))
      :ARG1 p
      :quant 3
      :ARG2-of ii
      :ARG1 (g / girl
            :age (t / temporal-quantity
                  :quant 1
                  :unit (y / year)))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / tuesday)))
